From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Thu, 4 Dec 2025 15:14:52 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] dma/clk/reset/sound: Add CIX Sky1 audio subsystem support

Add support for the CIX Sky1 audio subsystem including:

DMA-350 driver enhancements (drivers/dma/arm-dma350.c):
- Add clock and reset control support for platforms that require them
- Add pm_runtime support for power domain management
- Add device tree DMA controller registration via of_dma_controller_register()
- Add of_xlate function to translate DT dmas property to channels
- Add DMA_SLAVE and DMA_CYCLIC capabilities for peripheral DMA
- Add device_config callback for slave configuration
- Add stub prep_slave_sg and prep_dma_cyclic (full implementation pending)
- Support shared interrupt mode when per-channel IRQs unavailable
- Handle reset deassert before accessing hardware registers

AUDSS Clock Controller (drivers/clk/cix/clk-sky1-audss.c):
- New driver for Sky1 Audio Subsystem clock controller
- Provides clocks for I2S, DMA, HDA, DSP, timers, mailbox
- Composite clocks with mux, divider, and gate components
- Uses regmap for register access via parent syscon
- Runtime PM support with register save/restore
- Manages 6 parent clocks from SCMI and internal dividers
- Registers 41 clocks total including fixed dividers

AUDSS Reset Controller (drivers/reset/reset-sky1-audss.c):
- New driver for Sky1 Audio Subsystem reset controller
- Provides reset control for I2S, DMA, HDA, DSP, timers, mailbox
- Uses regmap for register access via parent syscon
- Supports 16 reset lines

I2S Drivers (sound/soc/cix/):
- cdns_i2s_mc.c: Cadence I2S multi-channel controller driver
- cdns_i2s_sc.c: Cadence I2S single-channel controller driver
- sky1-card.c: Sky1 ASoC machine driver for audio card
- card-utils.c/h: Common utilities for DAI link setup

Device Tree (arch/arm64/boot/dts/cix/sky1.dtsi):
- Add AUDSS syscon node with clock and reset controller children
- Add DMA-350 controller node at 0x7010000 with reset, clock, power-domain
- Add I2S controller nodes (I2S0-I2S9) with appropriate clock/reset/DMA refs
- Add sound card node linking I2S to HDMI audio codec

The audio subsystem uses:
- SCMI for parent clocks (audio_clk0-5) and power domain (SKY1_PD_AUDIO)
- ARM DMA-350 for audio DMA transfers
- Cadence I2S IP for audio interfaces

Current status:
- DMA-350 initializes and registers as OF DMA controller
- I2S drivers can request DMA channels (no longer stuck in deferred probe)
- Full DMA transfer implementation pending (prep functions return NULL)
- I2S probing fails at ASoC set_fmt (separate issue to investigate)
